{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":44018,"name":"Brian Knox","username":"najak3d","avatar_template":"https://avatars.discourse-cdn.com/v4/letter/n/6a8cbe/{size}.png","created_at":"2021-12-20T08:55:14.803Z","cooked":"\u003cp\u003eWe‚Äôre devising a Game Editor setup using Avalonia, with elix22‚Äôs \u003ca href=\"http://Urho.NET\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003eUrho.NET\u003c/a\u003e.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs the general scheme:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003col\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eUrho App is the main app, and owns the Main Window.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eIn Game Editor mode, we‚Äôre using Urho‚Äôs UI system to render a full-screen sprite inside which Avalonia is rendering.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eInside of Avalonia‚Äôs Dock Control sample, we have an Urho View 3D, which renders great.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003cli\u003eISSUE:  Since our Game UI is ALSO going to use Avalonia, we need for it to render inside the View3D game window.\u003c/li\u003e\n\u003c/ol\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eBut View3D doesn‚Äôt sport it‚Äôs own Urho UI.   We‚Äôd like a 2nd instance of Urho UI to place inside the View3D, and have it work the same as it does for the full screen now.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003ePerhaps I‚Äôm missing something; another/better way.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eFor now ‚Äì we have a work-around which is to simply use the SAME Urho.UI.Root to create the Sprite (which renders Avalonia), and place that Sprite overtop the View3D window, so that it appears to be a part of the View3D.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eThis seems to work fine, and performs well-enough - but the solution feels kludgy.   I think we‚Äôd prefer to have a separate UI.Root that runs inside the View3D itself.   (A UI inside the UI.)\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAnother idea that just popped into my head now is that maybe we can Parent the Game UI sprite to the View3D ‚Äì and maybe that resolves it, if there is relative-sizing/positioning ‚Äì so that if View3D resizes or moves ‚Äì the child Sprite inside it will move/resize in unison.   (OR‚Ä¶ we can just manually do this math, and create the same effect in C#).\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eHere‚Äôs a screenshot of our KLUDGE ‚Äì the UI sample we‚Äôre using here is crap ‚Äì it‚Äôs just a placeholder.   We have already figured out how to make this semi-transparent with click-through-to-scene.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"lightbox-wrapper\"\u003e\u003ca class=\"lightbox\" href=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/original/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c.jpeg\" data-download-href=\"/uploads/short-url/gEiIlr1fbKLRsfx3FlBFt2J89u4.jpeg?dl=1\" title=\"image\" rel=\"noopener nofollow ugc\"\u003e\u003cimg src=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c_2_690x366.jpeg\" alt=\"image\" data-base62-sha1=\"gEiIlr1fbKLRsfx3FlBFt2J89u4\" width=\"690\" height=\"366\" srcset=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c_2_690x366.jpeg, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c_2_1035x549.jpeg 1.5x, https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c_2_1380x732.jpeg 2x\" data-small-upload=\"https://global.discourse-cdn.com/standard17/uploads/urho3d/optimized/2X/7/74b10ce575f1b69fe43be4abcb07605d74a1d27c_2_10x10.png\"\u003e\u003cdiv class=\"meta\"\u003e\n\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-far-image svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#far-image\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\u003cspan class=\"filename\"\u003eimage\u003c/span\u003e\u003cspan class=\"informations\"\u003e1920√ó1020 106 KB\u003c/span\u003e\u003csvg class=\"fa d-icon d-icon-discourse-expand svg-icon\" aria-hidden=\"true\"\u003e\u003cuse href=\"#discourse-expand\"\u003e\u003c/use\u003e\u003c/svg\u003e\n\u003c/div\u0